                       Fifth Real-Time Linux Workshop
                                      
                             November 9-11 2003
                    Department of Computer Engineering 
                    Universidad Politecnica de Valencia 
                 Camino de Vera s/n Valencia, 46071, Spain
                                 and the
                     Real Time Linux Foundation Inc.
                                      

                              Call for papers 
                                      
  General
  
   Following the meetings of developers and users of real-time Linux in
   Vienna, Orlando, Milano and Boston, the Real-Time Linux Workshop 2003
   will be held in Valencia (DISCA, Universidad Politecnica de Valencia).
   If you are interested to participate in this up-coming workshop as
   speaker, we invite you to send an abstract on one of the following
   topics:
   
     modifications and variants of the GNU/Linux operating system,
   
     contributions and tools around and to real-time Linux variants,
   
     real-time Linux applications, in academia, research and industry,
   
     tools for embedding Linux or real-time Linux,
   
     embedded real-time Linux applications,
   
     work in progress reports,
   
     educational material on realtime linux.
   
  Important dates
  
   July 15, 2003 Abstract or paper draft
   September 30, 2003 Notification of acceptance
   October 15, 2003 Final paper
   November 10-11 Workshop
   
